{"id":1248,"date":"2022-02-21T17:04:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-21T17:04:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1248"},"modified":"2022-02-21T10:53:02","modified_gmt":"2022-02-21T10:53:02","slug":"configure-hostname-resolution","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1248","title":{"rendered":"Configure hostname resolution"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Hostname resolution makes it easy to locate a system on a large network.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Hostname Resolution<\/strong>&nbsp;refers to the process through which an assigned hostname is converted or resolved to its mapped IP Address so that networked hosts can communicate with each other.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This process can either be achieved locally on the host itself or remotely through a designated host configured to serve that purpose.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"249c\">Understanding DNS resolution and resolv.conf<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"69d2\">The\u00a0<strong>resolv.conf\u00a0<\/strong>configuration file contains information that allows a computer to convert human-readable alpha-numeric domain names (FQDN) into the machine-readable IP addresses (IPv4 or IPv6). The process of converting domain names to IP addresses is called\u00a0<strong><em>resolution, domain name resolution<\/em><\/strong>\u00a0or\u00a0<strong><em>DNS resolution.<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><code>resolv.conf<\/code>&nbsp;is part of the standard way to resolve a host name to an IP address. It is part of the resolver library.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are different ways to resolve your host name:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>files (specifically:&nbsp;<code>\/etc\/hosts<\/code>)<\/li><li>dns<\/li><li>NIS, NIS+ or yp<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The sequence in which they are used is in\u00a0<code>\/etc\/nsswitch.conf<\/code>. This normally says<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>hosts:      files dns\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>which means that the resolver library first looks in\u00a0<code>\/etc\/hosts<\/code>\u00a0and, if it cannot find it there, will use DNS.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"68\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-163.png?resize=640%2C68&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1254\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-163.png?w=736&amp;ssl=1 736w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-163.png?resize=300%2C32&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-163.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-163.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-163.png?resize=48%2C5&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now DNS will query a DNS server. Which one is determined by\u00a0<code>\/etc\/resolv.conf<\/code>. In addition, there are a number of additional parameters that you can use to help the DNS resolution, of which\u00a0<code>search<\/code>\u00a0(Try this domain first for the host) is probably the most used.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"configure-new-dns-resolution\">Configure new DNS resolution<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Using nmtui<\/strong> <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">nmutui<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to &#8220;edit a connection&#8221; > Ethernet &#8220;name of your interface&#8221; > Edit > DNS Servers and add a new one.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"435\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-160.png?resize=640%2C435&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1251\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-160.png?w=713&amp;ssl=1 713w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-160.png?resize=300%2C204&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-160.png?resize=24%2C16&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-160.png?resize=36%2C24&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-160.png?resize=48%2C33&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"68\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-161.png?resize=640%2C68&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1252\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-161.png?w=727&amp;ssl=1 727w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-161.png?resize=300%2C32&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-161.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-161.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-161.png?resize=48%2C5&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see the changes are still not applied and to do that we need to restart a network service.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl restart NetworkManager<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"77\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-162.png?resize=640%2C77&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1253\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-162.png?w=730&amp;ssl=1 730w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-162.png?resize=300%2C36&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-162.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-162.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-162.png?resize=48%2C6&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Hostname resolution makes it easy to locate a system on a large network.\u00a0 Hostname Resolution&nbsp;refers [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1246,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[397,190,450,451,449,220],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/rhsa-Manage-basic-networking.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1248"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?r